1
00:00:03,837 --> 00:00:05,771
My young friends, you're among the best

2
00:00:05,772 --> 00:00:06,939
and brightest in the land,

3
00:00:06,940 --> 00:00:10,209
but are you willing to obey and go?

4
00:00:10,210 --> 00:00:13,346
Are you willing to head the call?

5
00:00:13,347 --> 00:00:15,581
It matters not the field of service.

6
00:00:15,582 --> 00:00:17,483
What matters is your willingness to obey

7
00:00:17,484 --> 00:00:19,852
the Lord's command as found in Isaiah

8
00:00:19,853 --> 00:00:21,161
chapter six.

9
00:00:21,955 --> 00:00:24,290
Are you willing to take your talents and

10
00:00:24,291 --> 00:00:26,526
place them on the alter and say,

11
00:00:26,527 --> 00:00:30,339
"Here am I, Lord. Send me."

12
00:00:31,231 --> 00:00:33,833
It was a terribly painful moment,

13
00:00:33,834 --> 00:00:37,403
more painful than I care to remember.

14
00:00:37,404 --> 00:00:39,105
I felt I had nothing to offer God but

15
00:00:39,106 --> 00:00:41,807
a string of failures.

16
00:00:41,808 --> 00:00:45,381
What could He possibly want from me?

17
00:00:46,013 --> 00:00:47,713
The answer to that question will probably

18
00:00:47,714 --> 00:00:50,550
surprise you because there's a strength

19
00:00:50,551 --> 00:00:52,718
that can come from weakness.

20
00:00:52,719 --> 00:00:55,955
There's a strength that lies hidden in failure.

21
00:00:55,956 --> 00:00:59,563
You might not think so, but there is.

22
00:00:59,793 --> 00:01:02,364
I'm living proof.

23
00:02:31,018 --> 00:02:33,085
Uh, where's ma?

24
00:02:33,086 --> 00:02:35,087
She's up at the hill with your dad.

25
00:02:35,088 --> 00:02:37,123
They're about ready to move the house.

26
00:02:37,124 --> 00:02:38,524
They are?

27
00:02:38,525 --> 00:02:40,359
Don't go gettin' any fancy ideas.

28
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:41,894
Your mom said you need to stay here

29
00:02:41,895 --> 00:02:42,995
and do your chores.

30
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:43,872
Chores is done!

31
00:02:44,798 --> 00:02:46,141
Josh, come back here!

32
00:02:47,134 --> 00:02:48,200
I had known for a while

33
00:02:48,201 --> 00:02:49,902
they were going to move the house

34
00:02:49,903 --> 00:02:52,271
but I didn't know exactly when,

35
00:02:52,272 --> 00:02:54,473
and I was so excited.

36
00:02:54,474 --> 00:02:55,641
How were they going to do it?

37
00:02:55,642 --> 00:02:57,777
I was just a kid, what did I know?

38
00:02:57,778 --> 00:02:59,278
Was a helicopter going to come

39
00:02:59,279 --> 00:03:01,147
down from the sky, or airplanes

40
00:03:01,148 --> 00:03:02,815
fly over to lift the house up

41
00:03:02,816 --> 00:03:03,716
and take it away?

42
00:03:03,717 --> 00:03:05,217
This house belongs to me

43
00:03:05,218 --> 00:03:06,619
and it's stayin' here!

44
00:03:06,620 --> 00:03:09,922
Now I want you boys off'a my property!

45
00:03:09,923 --> 00:03:10,833
Keep working.

46
00:03:11,892 --> 00:03:13,292
Ain't you gonna do something?!

47
00:03:13,293 --> 00:03:15,494
I want these men off'a my property!

48
00:03:15,495 --> 00:03:16,629
- I'm sorry, Wllmot.

49
00:03:16,630 --> 00:03:18,097
According to this court order

50
00:03:18,098 --> 00:03:19,665
that house now belongs to Junior

51
00:03:19,666 --> 00:03:21,233
and he can move it if he has a mind to.

52
00:03:21,234 --> 00:03:22,735
I built that house!

53
00:03:22,736 --> 00:03:24,170
- And promised it to your son.

54
00:03:24,171 --> 00:03:25,638
The hell I did!

55
00:03:25,639 --> 00:03:28,574
- You were too drunk to remember!

56
00:03:28,575 --> 00:03:30,042
I have witnesses.

57
00:03:30,043 --> 00:03:31,977
Come on, we're taking those bushes.

58
00:03:31,978 --> 00:03:34,046
You ain't taking no bushes, Junior!

59
00:03:34,047 --> 00:03:35,617
Get! Get on out of here!

60
00:03:40,387 --> 00:03:41,921
I had no idea of the conflict

61
00:03:41,922 --> 00:03:43,856
unfolding that morning.

62
00:03:43,857 --> 00:03:45,324
I just figured the crowd I saw

63
00:03:45,325 --> 00:03:46,592
at the top of the hill meant we were

64
00:03:46,593 --> 00:03:48,834
going to have some kind of celebration.

65
00:03:49,496 --> 00:03:51,097
But instead of a party,

66
00:03:51,098 --> 00:03:52,898
I came face-to-face with the misery

67
00:03:52,899 --> 00:03:54,900
and dysfunction of my family

68
00:03:54,901 --> 00:03:56,836
played out in front of all of our neighbors

69
00:03:56,837 --> 00:03:59,004
and so-called friends.

70
00:03:59,005 --> 00:04:00,372
They had turned out to support

71
00:04:00,373 --> 00:04:02,683
my brother, Junior, against our parents.

72
00:04:03,276 --> 00:04:04,877
It was completely shameful

73
00:04:04,878 --> 00:04:06,979
and embarrassing and something

74
00:04:06,980 --> 00:04:10,018
inside me just broke me that day.

75
00:04:11,284 --> 00:04:12,785
I blanked out at that moment.

76
00:04:12,786 --> 00:04:15,121
My mind went numb.

77
00:04:15,122 --> 00:04:17,323
I think emotionally I snapped

78
00:04:17,324 --> 00:04:19,558
because I can't remember what happened

79
00:04:19,559 --> 00:04:21,794
over the next several minutes

80
00:04:21,795 --> 00:04:24,797
But my last conscious thought...

81
00:04:24,798 --> 00:04:27,166
I remember running down the hill

82
00:04:27,167 --> 00:04:28,567
in front of everyone

83
00:04:28,568 --> 00:04:31,048
just crying and screaming.

84
00:05:06,039 --> 00:05:08,178
They're all lies!

85
00:05:09,442 --> 00:05:12,753
If you cared, you wouldn't do this to me!

86
00:05:13,547 --> 00:05:14,780
Have you ever felt abandoned?

87
00:05:14,781 --> 00:05:17,650
I hate you, God! I hate you!

88
00:05:17,651 --> 00:05:19,118
Have you ever felt nobody cares

89
00:05:19,119 --> 00:05:21,156
whether you live or die?

90
00:05:21,588 --> 00:05:24,296
And I hate you dad!

91
00:05:25,859 --> 00:05:27,393
That's how I felt at eleven years old

92
00:05:27,394 --> 00:05:30,462
when I was hiding in the silo.

93
00:05:30,463 --> 00:05:33,465
I felt I had no one to turn to.

94
00:05:33,466 --> 00:05:37,036
I hate you! I hate you!

95
00:05:37,037 --> 00:05:39,405
And I became angry.

96
00:05:39,406 --> 00:05:42,908
I became angry at God if God even existed.

97
00:05:42,909 --> 00:05:44,677
And I damned him.

98
00:05:44,678 --> 00:05:46,988
I called him every name in the book.

99
00:05:49,015 --> 00:05:51,684
And I cursed and damned my father, too,

100
00:05:51,685 --> 00:05:55,223
because I felt that he had abandoned me.

101
00:06:03,663 --> 00:06:06,232
My father was an alcoholic.

102
00:06:06,233 --> 00:06:09,134
He was the town drunk.

103
00:06:09,135 --> 00:06:10,803
My mother was so overweight

104
00:06:10,804 --> 00:06:15,040
she was practically an invalid.

105
00:06:15,041 --> 00:06:19,251
One of my sisters committed suicide.

106
00:06:19,312 --> 00:06:20,980
My other sister joined the Army

107
00:06:20,981 --> 00:06:24,087
just to get away from home.

108
00:06:24,150 --> 00:06:26,819
My oldest brother, Wilmot,

109
00:06:26,820 --> 00:06:29,824
He actually sued my parents

110
00:06:29,890 --> 00:06:31,801
in a court of law.

111
00:06:31,858 --> 00:06:34,668
It wasn't a very happy home,

112
00:06:34,728 --> 00:06:37,363
and I can remember so often just

113
00:06:37,364 --> 00:06:39,465
feeling alone.

114
00:06:39,466 --> 00:06:41,969
Like I was just completely alone.

115
00:06:46,339 --> 00:06:50,709


116
00:06:50,710 --> 00:06:52,778
I was in that cell for about 3 hours,

117
00:06:52,779 --> 00:06:54,313
maybe more.

118
00:06:54,314 --> 00:06:57,116
And no one even came to look for me.

119
00:06:57,117 --> 00:07:00,252
Finally, I was just so hungry and thirsty,

120
00:07:00,253 --> 00:07:03,427
I climbed out and went home.

121
00:07:06,993 --> 00:07:10,065
I slammed the door shut on God that day.

122
00:07:11,197 --> 00:07:12,631
In fact, probably one of the greatest hurts

123
00:07:12,632 --> 00:07:14,900
was - is that I never ever wanted to go

124
00:07:14,901 --> 00:07:16,769
to a friend's house again.

125
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:18,871
I felt such shame.

126
00:07:18,872 --> 00:07:21,607
I think I just gave up on the notion that

127
00:07:21,608 --> 00:07:25,878
love is patient, or kind, or even

128
00:07:25,879 --> 00:07:28,414
rejoices in the truth.

129
00:07:28,415 --> 00:07:30,549
And to be honest with you,

130
00:07:30,550 --> 00:07:32,251
I never thought that door would ever

131
00:07:32,252 --> 00:07:34,289
open again.

132
00:08:29,509 --> 00:08:31,910
Josh, what are you doing out here?

133
00:08:31,911 --> 00:08:34,346
You need to start your chores, boy.

134
00:08:34,347 --> 00:08:36,156
Hurry up, now.

135
00:09:27,834 --> 00:09:30,869
All right cows, let's go!

136
00:09:30,870 --> 00:09:34,875
Come on, go! Come on, come on!

137
00:09:51,825 --> 00:09:53,659
Oh, what, what is that man doing

138
00:09:53,660 --> 00:09:55,427
with them cows now?

139
00:09:55,428 --> 00:09:58,170
It's worse than dealing with a small child.

140
00:09:58,231 --> 00:09:59,767
Him and his liquor!

141
00:10:19,219 --> 00:10:21,495
What the hell?

142
00:10:30,663 --> 00:10:32,531
I got chores of my own!

143
00:10:32,532 --> 00:10:33,766
I've got to come out and do

144
00:10:33,767 --> 00:10:35,610
your chores, too, I can see!

145
00:10:36,302 --> 00:10:38,646
What is going on here?

146
00:10:38,705 --> 00:10:40,739
Oh, Lord not again.

147
00:10:40,740 --> 00:10:42,341
Wilmot McDowell!

148
00:10:42,342 --> 00:10:43,542
Are you milking these cows

149
00:10:43,543 --> 00:10:45,978
or just trying to kill them?

150
00:10:45,979 --> 00:10:47,946
I got my own chores to do!

151
00:10:47,947 --> 00:10:50,188
Do I have to do everything around here?

152
00:10:51,017 --> 00:10:52,655
All you do around here is

153
00:10:52,719 --> 00:10:54,586
getting fatter by the day.

154
00:10:54,587 --> 00:10:56,855
- Useless old drunk!

155
00:10:56,856 --> 00:10:59,391
This cow's milked out right here, this one!

156
00:10:59,392 --> 00:11:00,926
You can't even take care of a cow

157
00:11:00,927 --> 00:11:01,905
for heaven's sake!

158
00:11:03,863 --> 00:11:08,863
(Edith screaming)

159
00:11:23,483 --> 00:11:25,656
Got your chores done, Edith? Huh?!

160
00:11:32,392 --> 00:11:33,292
I'll kill you!

161
00:11:33,293 --> 00:11:34,593
- No, Josh!
I'll kill you!

162
00:11:34,594 --> 00:11:38,630
Do you hear, me?!

163
00:11:38,631 --> 00:11:40,611
I swear you'll pay!

164
00:11:41,868 --> 00:11:43,848
You'll see!

165
00:11:47,273 --> 00:11:48,307
Josh!

166
00:11:48,308 --> 00:11:50,309
Oh, Josh.

167
00:11:50,310 --> 00:11:51,009
Mom.

168
00:11:51,010 --> 00:11:53,456
You can't do it. You can't do it.

169
00:11:54,948 --> 00:11:56,782
Just go get Wayne.

170
00:11:56,783 --> 00:11:57,659
Mom.

171
00:11:58,651 --> 00:11:59,356
Mom.

172
00:12:00,253 --> 00:12:01,520
He's, he's gonna change, son.

173
00:12:01,521 --> 00:12:03,755
I know he's gonna change.

174
00:12:03,756 --> 00:12:07,260
Just, just go get Wayne. Just get him.

175
00:12:22,075 --> 00:12:24,343
Crying's not going to do anyone any good,

176
00:12:24,344 --> 00:12:25,482
Josh.

177
00:12:25,678 --> 00:12:27,546
Wayne Bailey was used to my dad hurting

178
00:12:27,547 --> 00:12:28,423
my mom.

179
00:12:29,015 --> 00:12:30,358
It's your mother again, ain't it?

180
00:12:31,417 --> 00:12:34,421
He was used to me asking for his help.

181
00:12:37,757 --> 00:12:39,258
He worked in the house because

182
00:12:39,259 --> 00:12:41,159
mom was just too slow and too heavy

183
00:12:41,160 --> 00:12:43,436
for most of the household chores.

184
00:12:52,772 --> 00:12:53,839
I suppose he handled that side

185
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:55,285
of things well enough.

186
00:12:57,610 --> 00:13:00,056
It was the other things that he did.

187
00:13:05,485 --> 00:13:07,619
As far as handling my dad was concerned,

188
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:08,754
I didn't need help from Wayne

189
00:13:08,755 --> 00:13:10,291
or anyone else.

190
00:13:49,095 --> 00:13:50,195
When you grow up on a farm,

191
00:13:50,196 --> 00:13:52,431
You learn to do a lot of things as a kid.

192
00:13:52,432 --> 00:13:54,537
You also get pretty strong.

193
00:13:55,468 --> 00:13:56,935
If I knew friends were planning to come

194
00:13:56,936 --> 00:13:58,870
by the house, I took matters

195
00:13:58,871 --> 00:14:00,439
into my own hands.

196
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:02,240
Partly to avoid embarrassment

197
00:14:02,241 --> 00:14:04,409
from my dad, who was always drunk,

198
00:14:04,410 --> 00:14:05,877
and partly to pay him back

199
00:14:05,878 --> 00:14:07,721
for what he did to my mom.

200
00:14:09,882 --> 00:14:10,449
Josh, what are you doing?

201
00:14:10,450 --> 00:14:11,588
- Just stay there!
Josh, what are you doing?

202
00:14:16,122 --> 00:14:18,534
What are you doing -Ahhh!

203
00:14:20,727 --> 00:14:22,365
Josh I didn't mean to.

204
00:14:29,168 --> 00:14:30,704
<i>Josh...</i>

205
00:14:31,738 --> 00:14:33,939
Josh, I'm your father, Josh.

206
00:14:33,940 --> 00:14:35,112
Jo.

207
00:14:36,275 --> 00:14:39,654
Some father you are.

208
00:14:40,513 --> 00:14:42,748
Now, don't you make a sound.

209
00:14:42,749 --> 00:14:45,025
You hear me?!

210
00:14:45,485 --> 00:14:50,457


211
00:14:58,865 --> 00:15:01,400
Hello Mr. O'Brien. Hello Mrs. O'Brien.

212
00:15:01,401 --> 00:15:04,102
Howdy, Josh. Where's your dad?

213
00:15:04,103 --> 00:15:06,405
He, uh, he had to go into town,

214
00:15:06,406 --> 00:15:08,807
but my mom's inside. She's expecting you.

215
00:15:08,808 --> 00:15:10,509
Thank you, Josh.

216
00:15:10,510 --> 00:15:12,477
Come on in, folks!

217
00:15:12,478 --> 00:15:13,178
Come on in.

218
00:15:13,179 --> 00:15:14,679
Just in here taking the chicken out

219
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:18,127
of the oven. Have a seat over there.

220
00:15:18,885 --> 00:15:21,820
I would leave my dad in the barn all night.

221
00:15:21,821 --> 00:15:24,623
I don't know how many times I would do that.

222
00:15:24,624 --> 00:15:25,957
But I would do just about anything

223
00:15:25,958 --> 00:15:28,093
to humiliate him.

224
00:15:28,094 --> 00:15:30,629
I can remember watching him go out

225
00:15:30,630 --> 00:15:32,864
to hide his wine bottles and then

226
00:15:32,865 --> 00:15:34,733
I'd go out and urinate in them.

227
00:15:34,734 --> 00:15:38,270
One time the police pulled me off my dad

228
00:15:38,271 --> 00:15:39,571
when I was trying to choke him underneath

229
00:15:39,572 --> 00:15:40,572
the water in the bathtub.

230
00:15:40,573 --> 00:15:42,109
I hated him so much.

231
00:15:42,742 --> 00:15:44,042
I used to go to the bathroom and then

232
00:15:44,043 --> 00:15:45,784
stick his head in the t-

233
00:15:51,017 --> 00:15:54,653
...stick his head in the toilet and flush it.

234
00:15:54,654 --> 00:15:56,621
And as a kid, all I ever wanted

235
00:15:56,622 --> 00:16:00,125
was to stop my dad from hurting my mother,

236
00:16:00,126 --> 00:16:02,003
and I couldn't do it.

237
00:16:18,177 --> 00:16:20,312
He never retaliated directly.

238
00:16:20,313 --> 00:16:24,516
He could have. I mean I was still a kid.

239
00:16:24,517 --> 00:16:26,084
I think when he sobered up,

240
00:16:26,085 --> 00:16:28,620
even thought he didn't stay sober long,

241
00:16:28,621 --> 00:16:30,288
he must have realized what he was doing

242
00:16:30,289 --> 00:16:32,090
to my mom and the family.

243
00:16:32,091 --> 00:16:34,426
I think he was ashamed.

244
00:16:34,427 --> 00:16:39,399
I don't know for sure, but life went on.

245
00:17:55,374 --> 00:17:57,786
You got them rolls in there?

246
00:18:00,379 --> 00:18:02,247
Ah, here we go.

247
00:18:02,248 --> 00:18:04,883
All right, fellas, we got some nice hot rolls

248
00:18:04,884 --> 00:18:08,653
for you. Here we go.

249
00:18:08,654 --> 00:18:09,955
And if you want to start that butter

250
00:18:09,956 --> 00:18:11,663
down this side.

251
00:18:11,857 --> 00:18:14,359
And Josh, your father and I have to talk

252
00:18:14,360 --> 00:18:16,704
to you after supper.

253
00:18:39,919 --> 00:18:43,321
How are you, my darlings?

254
00:18:43,322 --> 00:18:44,823
Yes?

255
00:18:44,824 --> 00:18:46,725
Yes? Oh my.

256
00:18:46,726 --> 00:18:51,698
Yes. Beautiful. I have something for you.

257
00:18:54,667 --> 00:18:58,205
I want you to obey Wayne. No excuses.

258
00:18:58,938 --> 00:19:00,905
How long will you be gone?

259
00:19:00,906 --> 00:19:04,042
Well, I don't know, a week maybe.

260
00:19:04,043 --> 00:19:05,750
Ten days at the most.

261
00:19:06,579 --> 00:19:08,380
That's a long time.

262
00:19:08,381 --> 00:19:09,748
What ails you, son?

263
00:19:09,749 --> 00:19:10,982
Your dad and I have made trips

264
00:19:10,983 --> 00:19:12,550
like this before.

265
00:19:12,551 --> 00:19:14,286
Wayne knows how to take good care of you.

266
00:19:14,287 --> 00:19:16,096
You just do what he says.

267
00:19:16,489 --> 00:19:17,989
Why don't I come with you?

268
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:19,224
I came with you once before.

269
00:19:19,225 --> 00:19:20,625
- Joslin David McDowell,
I came with you once before.

270
00:19:20,626 --> 00:19:21,693
You cannot go with us.

271
00:19:21,694 --> 00:19:24,262
You're starting school next week!

272
00:19:24,263 --> 00:19:25,799
And I want you to listen to me.

273
00:19:27,066 --> 00:19:29,234
When I get home, I am going to ask Wayne

274
00:19:29,235 --> 00:19:31,403
how you behaved and if I hear you didn't

275
00:19:31,404 --> 00:19:33,505
listen to him, I'm going to give you

276
00:19:33,506 --> 00:19:35,307
a good thrashing. Do you understand me?

