00:34:21,560 --> 00:34:23,369
to prove my main points.

552
00:34:23,862 --> 00:34:25,863
And funny how these things happen...

553
00:34:25,864 --> 00:34:28,899
I began to get the idea of going to Europe

554
00:34:28,900 --> 00:34:31,068
to study original manuscripts that I knew

555
00:34:31,069 --> 00:34:32,570
were housed in some of the libraries

556
00:34:32,571 --> 00:34:33,345
over there.

557
00:34:34,306 --> 00:34:37,116
It was early summer 1958.

558
00:34:38,877 --> 00:34:41,479
I had my own money, that wasn't a problem,

559
00:34:41,480 --> 00:34:43,514
so I flew to England and just began to read

560
00:34:43,515 --> 00:34:45,816
everything I could get my hands on.

561
00:34:45,817 --> 00:34:48,627
I read the works of many well-known skeptics.

562
00:34:49,488 --> 00:34:51,589
I also examined the writings of a smaller

563
00:34:51,590 --> 00:34:54,158
group of individuals, all of them proficient

564
00:34:54,159 --> 00:34:56,627
in their areas of expertise,

565
00:34:56,628 --> 00:34:58,262
who started out as unbelievers

566
00:34:58,263 --> 00:35:00,564
and later became Christians.

567
00:35:00,565 --> 00:35:01,999
This intrigued me,

568
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:03,834
and I wanted to find out why.

569
00:35:03,835 --> 00:35:05,473
What led them to change?

570
00:35:06,538 --> 00:35:07,972
There was Lord Lyttleton, who

571
00:35:07,973 --> 00:35:10,808
later became Chancellor of the Exchequer,

572
00:35:10,809 --> 00:35:14,578
Gilbert West, Sir William Ramsey,

573
00:35:14,579 --> 00:35:17,715
Frank Morison, <i>C.S.</i> Lewis...

574
00:35:17,716 --> 00:35:20,551
all of them educated successful men

575
00:35:20,552 --> 00:35:21,852
- and skeptics -

576
00:35:21,853 --> 00:35:23,621
who became believers after carefully

577
00:35:23,622 --> 00:35:25,226
studying the evidence.

578
00:35:27,659 --> 00:35:30,194
On the same trip, I went to Germany,

579
00:35:30,195 --> 00:35:32,903
France and Switzerland.

580
00:35:34,165 --> 00:35:36,333
I'd go into various museums and libraries

581
00:35:36,334 --> 00:35:38,402
and look into the glass display cases

582
00:35:38,403 --> 00:35:41,038
holding rare books and manuscripts.

583
00:35:41,039 --> 00:35:42,706
I couldn't read Greek or Hebrew,

584
00:35:42,707 --> 00:35:46,677
but I knew those manuscripts were real.

585
00:35:46,678 --> 00:35:48,988
And significance of each one.

586
00:35:51,383 --> 00:35:52,817
I made my way back to England,

587
00:35:52,818 --> 00:35:55,019
and just a day or two before my return

588
00:35:55,020 --> 00:35:57,588
trip to the States, I went to a library

589
00:35:57,589 --> 00:35:59,535
on the northeastern edge of London.

590
00:36:00,158 --> 00:36:01,492
It was a small library

591
00:36:01,493 --> 00:36:02,860
someone had told me about,

592
00:36:02,861 --> 00:36:04,695
and it had several books and manuscripts

593
00:36:04,696 --> 00:36:06,198
I wanted to study.

594
00:36:07,032 --> 00:36:10,605
By this time, I was tired, really tired.

595
00:36:11,336 --> 00:36:14,171
I remember it was about 6:30 in the evening,

596
00:36:14,172 --> 00:36:15,673
and I leaned back in my chair,

597
00:36:15,674 --> 00:36:17,508
put my hands behind my head

598
00:36:17,509 --> 00:36:19,209
and said out loud,

599
00:36:19,210 --> 00:36:21,087
- It's true.
"It's true"

600
00:36:24,850 --> 00:36:25,954
I said it again

601
00:36:26,384 --> 00:36:27,362
It's true.

602
00:36:28,119 --> 00:36:28,986
...And again.

603
00:36:28,987 --> 00:36:29,829
- It's true!
...and again.

604
00:36:31,189 --> 00:36:33,100
Shhhh...

605
00:36:36,661 --> 00:36:38,529
I had started my journey as an obnoxious,

606
00:36:38,530 --> 00:36:40,698
agnositic university student

607
00:36:40,699 --> 00:36:43,233
who thought Christians were airheads.

608
00:36:43,234 --> 00:36:44,768
I had set out to refute their beliefs

609
00:36:44,769 --> 00:36:46,715
and disprove the resurrection.

610
00:36:47,205 --> 00:36:48,672
But after all my research,

611
00:36:48,673 --> 00:36:50,374
in spite of my prejudice,

612
00:36:50,375 --> 00:36:53,344
I realized I didn't have a valid defense.

613
00:36:53,345 --> 00:36:55,179
The historical evidence all pointed

614
00:36:55,180 --> 00:36:57,281
the other way, and I realized

615
00:36:57,282 --> 00:36:59,350
my rejection of the Bible and Christianity

616
00:36:59,351 --> 00:37:03,060
was based more on emotion than intellect.

617
00:37:04,122 --> 00:37:06,857
I wasn't ready to become a Christian,

618
00:37:06,858 --> 00:37:07,958
but I had to admit there was

619
00:37:07,959 --> 00:37:09,996
compelling evidence to consider,

620
00:37:10,629 --> 00:37:13,235
evidence that demanded a verdict.

621
00:37:21,306 --> 00:37:23,273
There came one running,

622
00:37:23,274 --> 00:37:24,942
and kneeled to him, and asked...

623
00:37:24,943 --> 00:37:25,843
- Back in Michigan,
and kneeled to him, and asked...

624
00:37:25,844 --> 00:37:28,445
I continued my college studies

625
00:37:28,446 --> 00:37:30,614
and began attending a small church called

626
00:37:30,615 --> 00:37:32,616
Factoryville Bible Church.

627
00:37:32,617 --> 00:37:35,185
The Pastor's name was Fay Logan.

628
00:37:35,186 --> 00:37:36,987
He knew what I'd been going through, and

629
00:37:36,988 --> 00:37:39,356
one day he prepared a special sermon

630
00:37:39,357 --> 00:37:41,158
Just for me.

631
00:37:41,159 --> 00:37:42,860
But let's be clear,

632
00:37:42,861 --> 00:37:47,861
God's salvation is not an intellectual exercise.

633
00:37:48,466 --> 00:37:52,703
We are saved by faith and trust in Christ.

634
00:37:52,704 --> 00:37:55,272
So, let me ask you,

635
00:37:55,273 --> 00:37:57,141
are you ready to recieve the gift

636
00:37:57,142 --> 00:38:00,711
of eternal life that Jesus is offering you

637
00:38:00,712 --> 00:38:05,482
right now? Do you believe?

638
00:38:05,483 --> 00:38:08,318
Are you ready to commit?

639
00:38:08,319 --> 00:38:09,920
Let's review what that commitment

640
00:38:09,921 --> 00:38:11,689
will involve.

641
00:38:11,690 --> 00:38:13,724
I acknowledge I am a sinner

642
00:38:13,725 --> 00:38:15,692
in need of salvation.

643
00:38:15,693 --> 00:38:19,129
Secondly, I believe in my heart

644
00:38:19,130 --> 00:38:22,733
that God did raise Jesus from the dead.

645
00:38:22,734 --> 00:38:26,236
Thirdly, I confess Jesus as my Lord

646
00:38:26,237 --> 00:38:28,238
and my God.

647
00:38:28,239 --> 00:38:31,075
I knew I needed to respond, but I couldn't.

648
00:38:31,076 --> 00:38:34,078
I was afraid.

649
00:38:34,079 --> 00:38:36,647
By receiving Christ as Savior and Lord,

650
00:38:36,648 --> 00:38:39,383
I'd be committing intellectual suicide.

651
00:38:39,384 --> 00:38:42,052
I was also afraid of what my friends would say.

652
00:38:42,053 --> 00:38:44,788
I was afraid of what they'd think.

653
00:38:44,789 --> 00:38:47,691
The Holy Spirit welcomes you to come

654
00:38:47,692 --> 00:38:50,494
and trust Jesus as your personal

655
00:38:50,495 --> 00:38:52,062
Lord and Savior.

656
00:38:52,063 --> 00:38:53,230
Who will come?

657
00:38:53,231 --> 00:38:55,766
And then, thank God, one of those friends

658
00:38:55,767 --> 00:38:58,235
leaned over and asked me a question.

659
00:38:58,236 --> 00:39:00,443
Do you want me to go with you?

660
00:39:15,587 --> 00:39:17,354
People think I became a Christian through

661
00:39:17,355 --> 00:39:20,097
the intellectual route. That's not true.

662
00:39:20,892 --> 00:39:22,993
All the study, all the research,

663
00:39:22,994 --> 00:39:25,763
that was God's way of getting my attention

664
00:39:25,764 --> 00:39:28,665
and I don't downplay it because without it

665
00:39:28,666 --> 00:39:29,967
I would never have considered

666
00:39:29,968 --> 00:39:32,175
the Bible's message.

667
00:39:38,176 --> 00:39:42,479
Josh, this Bible is for you.

668
00:39:42,480 --> 00:39:44,414
The door I had closed on God as an

669
00:39:44,415 --> 00:39:47,017
eleven-year-old, cracked open again

670
00:39:47,018 --> 00:39:49,186
and I began to learn that God is love,

671
00:39:49,187 --> 00:39:50,854
and he loves me.

672
00:39:50,855 --> 00:39:52,089
That he's passionate about having

673
00:39:52,090 --> 00:39:53,957
a relationship with me.

674
00:39:53,958 --> 00:39:55,559
And from that day forward

675
00:39:55,560 --> 00:39:57,094
with Pastor Logan's help

676
00:39:57,095 --> 00:40:00,702
I began to learn about the Christian life.

677
00:40:12,744 --> 00:40:14,211
But it wasn't the evidence that brought

678
00:40:14,212 --> 00:40:16,613
me to God.

679
00:40:16,614 --> 00:40:18,787
It was his love.

680
00:40:24,455 --> 00:40:27,257
"I have loved you with an everlasting love;

681
00:40:27,258 --> 00:40:30,034
with tender kindness I have drawn you."

682
00:40:31,529 --> 00:40:36,376
That's what God in his mercy did for me.

683
00:40:44,842 --> 00:40:45,843
There he is now.

684
00:41:08,500 --> 00:41:11,802
Josh, this is my girlfriend, Gail.

685
00:41:11,803 --> 00:41:13,077
Nice to meet you.

686
00:41:13,605 --> 00:41:15,672
I did not want to love my father

687
00:41:15,673 --> 00:41:17,241
or forgive him.

688
00:41:17,242 --> 00:41:19,776
I wanted to continue to hate him.

689
00:41:19,777 --> 00:41:21,445
I believed he had killed my mother

690
00:41:21,446 --> 00:41:23,614
and destroyed our family.

691
00:41:23,615 --> 00:41:25,382
For years, I'd gone to bed at night

692
00:41:25,383 --> 00:41:26,683
dreaming up ways to kill him

693
00:41:26,684 --> 00:41:29,052
without being caught by the police,

694
00:41:29,053 --> 00:41:31,421
and here I was, a new Christian,

695
00:41:31,422 --> 00:41:33,333
still determined to hate him.

696
00:41:36,761 --> 00:41:37,961
<i>So...</i>

697
00:41:37,962 --> 00:41:40,875
- Dad, I have something to say to you.

698
00:41:48,106 --> 00:41:49,744
Dad, I love you.

699
00:41:52,010 --> 00:41:54,111
I don't I know who was more in shock,

700
00:41:54,112 --> 00:41:55,946
him hearing what I said,

701
00:41:55,947 --> 00:41:58,015
or me saying the words.

702
00:41:58,016 --> 00:42:00,417
That's when I knew it was true.

703
00:42:00,418 --> 00:42:03,220
I was used to loving those I loved,

704
00:42:03,221 --> 00:42:04,888
but I never had the capacity to love

705
00:42:04,889 --> 00:42:06,957
someone I hated.

706
00:42:06,958 --> 00:42:08,792
I hated my father, and now

707
00:42:08,793 --> 00:42:11,461
I was overcome by love for him.

708
00:42:11,462 --> 00:42:12,829
Christianity was real.

709
00:42:12,830 --> 00:42:14,400
- Josh, how is college?
Christianity was real.

710
00:42:15,333 --> 00:42:17,000
Knowing it was true, however,

711
00:42:17,001 --> 00:42:18,235
even knowing that God

712
00:42:18,236 --> 00:42:20,170
loved me unconditionally

713
00:42:20,171 --> 00:42:21,939
didn't make some things any easier

714
00:42:21,940 --> 00:42:23,044
to deal with.

715
00:42:24,475 --> 00:42:28,979
I can't, Pastor. I just can't.

716
00:42:28,980 --> 00:42:30,847
It goes too deep.

717
00:42:30,848 --> 00:42:32,115
Josh.

718
00:42:32,116 --> 00:42:33,686
If this is Christianity,

719
00:42:35,586 --> 00:42:37,220
maybe I should hang it up.

720
00:42:37,221 --> 00:42:38,564
I can't.

721
00:42:40,391 --> 00:42:41,625
I'm sorry, Pastor.

722
00:42:41,626 --> 00:42:43,867
This is just too much to ask.

723
00:42:44,729 --> 00:42:46,504
I'm not asking you, Josh.

724
00:42:49,701 --> 00:42:51,647
No one understands.

725
00:43:07,018 --> 00:43:08,785
"And when they were come to the place

726
00:43:08,786 --> 00:43:10,988
which is called Calvary,

727
00:43:10,989 --> 00:43:14,858
there they crucified him and the malefactors,

728
00:43:14,859 --> 00:43:16,093
one on the right hand

729
00:43:16,094 --> 00:43:17,961
and the other on the left.

730
00:43:17,962 --> 00:43:22,132
Then said Jesus, 'Father, forgive them

731
00:43:22,133 --> 00:43:25,080
for they know not what they do."'

732
00:43:33,978 --> 00:43:35,579
Altogether, it was a process

733
00:43:35,580 --> 00:43:37,218
of about six months.

734
00:43:38,716 --> 00:43:40,717
And without Pastor Logan's patience

735
00:43:40,718 --> 00:43:43,460
and wisdom, I'd never had done it.

736
00:43:44,455 --> 00:43:48,525
Even when I did, I had no emotion about it.

737
00:43:48,526 --> 00:43:52,028
I did it by faith, out of obedience,

738
00:43:52,029 --> 00:43:54,441
knowing it was the right thing to do.

739
00:43:57,602 --> 00:43:59,236
I remember hoping I wouldn't be able

740
00:43:59,237 --> 00:44:01,581
to find out where he lived.

741
00:44:02,740 --> 00:44:04,276
But I did find out,

742
00:44:05,643 --> 00:44:07,811
and I called him up and I told him

743
00:44:07,812 --> 00:44:09,814
I was coming to see him.

744
00:44:52,390 --> 00:44:53,664
<i>Josh...</i>

745
00:44:54,725 --> 00:44:55,897
Wayne.

746
00:44:57,929 --> 00:45:01,433
Wayne, what you did to me was evil.

747
00:45:03,701 --> 00:45:05,874
And you know it was evil.

748
00:45:07,972 --> 00:45:08,780
But I've-

749
00:45:10,775 --> 00:45:14,244
I've come to know Christ as my Savior,

750
00:45:14,245 --> 00:45:16,413
my Lord.

751
00:45:16,414 --> 00:45:18,792
And I've come here to tell you...

752
00:45:21,452 --> 00:45:22,552
I've come here to tell you that

753
00:45:22,553 --> 00:45:25,432
Christ died as much for you as he did for me.

754
00:45:26,691 --> 00:45:28,602
I forgive you, Wayne.

755
00:45:42,507 --> 00:45:44,009
One more thing, Wayne.

756
00:45:46,911 --> 00:45:47,911
Don't let me ever hear of you

757
00:45:47,912 --> 00:45:49,858
touching a young man again.

758
00:45:50,915 --> 00:45:52,189
You'll regret it.

759
00:47:02,320 --> 00:47:07,123
In Hebrews, Jesus is accepted...

760
00:47:07,124 --> 00:47:10,060
Well, the bridge, Josh, I think is love.

761
00:47:10,061 --> 00:47:11,494
It's not a line in the sand.

762
00:47:11,495 --> 00:47:15,298
It's a relationship - a personal relationship.

763
00:47:15,299 --> 00:47:17,279
I like what Martin Luther said,

764
00:47:17,768 --> 00:47:19,736
"God writes the gospel not in the bible alone

765
00:47:19,737 --> 00:47:23,073
but also on the trees and the flowers;

766
00:47:23,074 --> 00:47:25,384
on the clouds and the stars."

767
00:47:26,611 --> 00:47:28,056
I've been thinking, Josh.

768
00:47:28,579 --> 00:47:29,387
Uh-oh.

769
00:47:30,348 --> 00:47:31,381
I think you need to transfer

770
00:47:31,382 --> 00:47:32,849
to Wheaten College.

771
00:47:32,850 --> 00:47:34,551
Wheaten College, where's that?

772
00:47:34,552 --> 00:47:35,685
Outside Chicago.

773
00:47:35,686 --> 00:47:35,785
- Yeah?
Outside Chicago.

774
00:47:35,786 --> 00:47:37,721
- Oh yeah?
It's where Billy Graham went to school.

775
00:47:37,722 --> 00:47:38,288
<i>Hmm...</i>

776
00:47:38,289 --> 00:47:40,323
It'll demand a lot out of you academically,

777
00:47:40,324 --> 00:47:42,592
but I think you're up to the challenge.

778
00:47:42,593 --> 00:47:43,126
You know, Pastor,

779
00:47:43,127 --> 00:47:44,694
I've been thinking of studying law?

780
00:47:44,695 --> 00:47:45,262
Really?

781
00:47:45,263 --> 00:47:45,862
Yeah.

782
00:47:45,863 --> 00:47:47,297
Well, whatever you decide to do,

783
00:47:47,298 --> 00:47:50,370
Wheaten can help you excel. I, <i>uh...</i>

784
00:48:08,519 --> 00:48:10,954
At Wheaten, I had time for two things:

785
00:48:10,955 --> 00:48:12,789
Study and work.

786
00:48:12,790 --> 00:48:14,724
I had a part-time job in the afternoons

787
00:48:14,725 --> 00:48:16,393
delivering administrative records

788
00:48:16,394 --> 00:48:18,237
for local high schools.

789
00:49:14,252 --> 00:49:16,186
As a result of the accident,

790
00:49:16,187 --> 00:49:18,021
the ligaments in my neck were torn loose

791
00:49:18,022 --> 00:49:20,468
and my lower back severly injured.

792
00:49:27,198 --> 00:49:29,132
After four days in Intensive Care,

793
00:49:29,133 --> 00:49:30,867
I spent another week and a half

794
00:49:30,868 --> 00:49:32,040
in the hospital.

795
00:49:51,222 --> 00:49:53,323
The doctors realized my recovery would be

796
00:49:53,324 --> 00:49:55,091
gradual, and they decided

797
00:49:55,092 --> 00:49:56,833
I should go home to mend.

798
00:50:01,899 --> 00:50:04,300
Ironically, the man who hit me

799
00:50:04,301 --> 00:50:06,406
was a drunk driver.

800
00:50:47,011 --> 00:50:48,711
The plan was for me to stay at home

801
00:50:48,712 --> 00:50:50,953
where I'd be looked after by a nurse,

802
00:50:51,849 --> 00:50:55,058
but the nurse was late the day of my arrival.

803
00:50:57,855 --> 00:51:00,597
My father met the ambulance, instead.

804
00:51:19,743 --> 00:51:21,484
Bring him in here, fellas.

805
00:51:22,380 --> 00:51:25,361
We've got, uh, the furniture out.

806
00:52:05,489 --> 00:52:06,331
Thank you.

807
00:52:34,819 --> 00:52:36,219
About five minutes had passed

808
00:52:36,220 --> 00:52:38,321
when my dad entered the room.

809
00:52:38,322 --> 00:52:40,456
He didn't actually walk into the room,

810
00:52:40,457 --> 00:52:42,125
He stood in the doorway.

811
00:52:42,126 --> 00:52:44,093
I couldn't move my head,

812
00:52:44,094 --> 00:52:45,462
but I could just make him out

813
00:52:45,463 --> 00:52:47,568
through the corner of one eye.

814
00:52:48,532 --> 00:52:50,603
There were two things I noticed right away.

815
00:52:51,335 --> 00:52:53,436
One, he was sober,

816
00:52:53,437 --> 00:52:55,739
and the other, he was crying.

817
00:52:55,740 --> 00:52:57,940
I couldn't move any part of my body

818
00:52:57,941 --> 00:52:59,609
except my eyes.

819
00:52:59,610 --> 00:53:01,778
He just pace back and forth,

820
00:53:01,779 --> 00:53:04,013
no dialogue, nothing.

821
00:53:04,014 --> 00:53:07,154
I just followed him as best I could.

822
00:53:16,093 --> 00:53:17,538
<i>Josh...</i>

823
00:53:20,364 --> 00:53:21,536
HOW.

824
00:53:21,999 --> 00:53:26,971
How could you ever love a father like me?

825
00:53:38,883 --> 00:53:40,590
<i>Dad...</i>

826
00:53:51,762 --> 00:53:54,038
I've learned one thing.

827
00:53:55,332 --> 00:54:00,543
God became man, and his name is Jesus.

828
00:54:03,207 --> 00:54:05,608
Jesus is passionate to have a relationship

829
00:54:05,609 --> 00:54:07,885
with you.

830
00:54:18,556 --> 00:54:20,627
He left the room and was gone.

831
00:54:21,458 --> 00:54:22,525
I don't know, maybe

832
00:54:22,526 --> 00:54:24,369
forty-five minutes passed.

833
00:54:25,663 --> 00:54:28,542
Then, he came back into the room.

834
00:54:38,676 --> 00:54:39,814
Josh,

835
00:54:42,179 --> 00:54:44,881
If Jesus can do in my life

836
00:54:44,882 --> 00:54:48,084
what I've seen him do in yours,

837
00:54:48,085 --> 00:54:50,258
then I want to know him.

838
00:54:53,123 --> 00:54:55,797
You need to ask him into your life, dad.

839
00:54:58,862 --> 00:55:02,173
Open your hear to him and pray.

840
00:55:06,904 --> 00:55:08,076
God,

841
00:55:09,173 --> 00:55:10,373
if you are God,

842
00:55:10,374 --> 00:55:12,475
My dad just prayed a simple prayer,

843
00:55:12,476 --> 00:55:13,810
a farmer's prayer I call it,

844
00:55:13,811 --> 00:55:15,313
very down to earth.

845
00:55:15,712 --> 00:55:17,180
All I could do was cry.

846
00:55:17,181 --> 00:55:19,682
Then, please,

847
00:55:19,683 --> 00:55:21,321
come in.

848
00:55:50,214 --> 00:55:52,415
When I came to Christ, my life changed over

849
00:55:52,416 --> 00:55:55,151
about a period of a year; year and a half.

850
00:55:55,152 --> 00:55:57,654
But when my father made that decision,

851
00:55:57,655 --> 00:55:59,355
the change was immediate.

852
00:55:59,356 --> 00:56:02,325
I saw him change right before my eyes.

853
00:56:02,326 --> 00:56:04,160
It was like somebody reached down and

854
00:56:04,161 --> 00:56:06,396
turned on a lightbulb in his life.

855
00:56:06,397 --> 00:56:08,197
And you know, only once after that

856
00:56:08,198 --> 00:56:13,198
did he ever touch alcohol, and he got it

857
00:56:13,470 --> 00:56:15,838
All of you remember the way I used to be,

858
00:56:15,839 --> 00:56:17,340
I was the town drunk.

859
00:56:17,341 --> 00:56:19,876
I was an embarrassment to my family.

860
00:56:19,877 --> 00:56:22,078
Tom, you were there on the hill that day

861
00:56:22,079 --> 00:56:24,046
when Junior was moving the house;

862
00:56:24,047 --> 00:56:26,584
stumbling, falling down drunk.

863
00:56:27,251 --> 00:56:28,451
I was an embarrassment.

864
00:56:28,452 --> 00:56:30,153
And you know my wife is gone now,

865
00:56:30,154 --> 00:56:31,788
I can't make it up to her, but I can tell you

866
00:56:31,789 --> 00:56:33,289
one thing, and it happened right

867
00:56:33,290 --> 00:56:36,893
here in this diner, was when my son, Josh,

868
00:56:36,894 --> 00:56:40,863
said to me, "Dad, I love you."

869
00:56:40,864 --> 00:56:42,265
And those were his exact words,

870
00:56:42,266 --> 00:56:44,967
"Dad, I love you." And that's...

871
00:56:44,968 --> 00:56:46,536
As a result of my dad's decision

872
00:56:46,537 --> 00:56:49,238
to trust Christ, scores of people in our town

873
00:56:49,239 --> 00:56:51,274
and the surrounding area came to know

874
00:56:51,275 --> 00:56:53,543
Jesus Christ as savior and Lord.

875
00:56:53,544 --> 00:56:55,278
All because of the changed life

876
00:56:55,279 --> 00:56:57,747
of the town drunk.

877
00:56:57,748 --> 00:57:00,991
I just wish my mother could have seen it.

878
00:57:01,818 --> 00:57:06,155
Fourteen months later, my father died.

879
00:57:06,156 --> 00:57:07,690
Three-fourths of his stomach had to be

880
00:57:07,691 --> 00:57:11,160
cut out, his entire liver was destroyed

881
00:57:11,161 --> 00:57:13,763
through thirty-some years of drinking.

882
00:57:13,764 --> 00:57:15,398
I was at Wheaten College when I got

883
00:57:15,399 --> 00:57:18,668
the news - which brings me back

884
00:57:18,669 --> 00:57:20,808
to where our story began.

885
00:57:24,074 --> 00:57:26,709
I had run out of Edman Chapel that evening.

886
00:57:26,710 --> 00:57:28,878
"Who will go?" the chapel speaker had said,

887
00:57:28,879 --> 00:57:31,180
quoting the prophet Isaiah.

888
00:57:31,181 --> 00:57:33,049
"Who will make their abilities available

889
00:57:33,050 --> 00:57:36,953
to God?" It sure wasn't going to be me,

890
00:57:36,954 --> 00:57:40,265
even if I was a student at Wheaten College.

891
00:57:43,060 --> 00:57:45,628
I still had feelings of inferiority,

892
00:57:45,629 --> 00:57:48,064
I still carried the scars of abuse

893
00:57:48,065 --> 00:57:51,300
and violence and family brokenness.

894
00:57:51,301 --> 00:57:53,836
Yeah, sure, I might succeed in hiding these

895
00:57:53,837 --> 00:57:56,205
things from others, but how could I

896
00:57:56,206 --> 00:57:58,207
hide them from myself?

897
00:57:58,208 --> 00:57:59,275
I remember thinking,

898
00:57:59,276 --> 00:58:01,511
"Well, maybe I should jusk walk away.

899
00:58:01,512 --> 00:58:03,512
Maybe I should leave the faith."

900
00:58:03,513 --> 00:58:08,513
All I'd ever heard as a Christian was that

901
00:58:09,319 --> 00:58:10,887
for his glory.

902
00:58:10,888 --> 00:58:13,456
That created a huge problem for me.

903
00:58:13,457 --> 00:58:15,925
I felt I had nothing to offer God

904
00:58:15,926 --> 00:58:18,532
but weakness and failure.

905
00:58:20,030 --> 00:58:23,699
My life story didn't have a fairy tale ending.

906
00:58:23,700 --> 00:58:25,167
And then I did something I thought

907
00:58:25,168 --> 00:58:29,005
I'd never do. I stopped and said,

908
00:58:29,006 --> 00:58:32,954
God, all I have are failures

909
00:58:34,244 --> 00:58:36,345
But if you can take my weaknesses

910
00:58:36,346 --> 00:58:38,587
and glorify yourself through them,

911
00:58:40,184 --> 00:58:43,358
I'll serve you with every breath I breathe.

912
00:58:44,921 --> 00:58:46,923
And that's the story, my friend.

913
00:58:47,424 --> 00:58:49,325
That's the story of how God saved me

914
00:58:49,326 --> 00:58:51,094
from destruction.

915
00:58:51,095 --> 00:58:53,362
How he chose the foolish and simple things

916
00:58:53,363 --> 00:58:56,310
to confound the strong and wise.

917
00:58:57,501 --> 00:59:00,948
The rest, I guess you'd say, is history.

918
01:00:28,992 --> 01:00:31,905
Maybe you can identify with pan of my story.

919
01:00:32,663 --> 01:00:35,200
Alcoholic or drug addicted parents,

920
01:00:35,832 --> 01:00:36,970
abuse,

921
01:00:37,501 --> 01:00:40,236
or that sense of loneliness where

922
01:00:40,237 --> 01:00:43,072
you feel like it wouldn't matter to anyone

923
01:00:43,073 --> 01:00:44,746
if you lived or died.

924
01:00:45,509 --> 01:00:47,716
Or that hopelessness

925
01:00:48,712 --> 01:00:50,579
that comes from that feeling that

926
01:00:50,580 --> 01:00:52,615
God just can't forgive me

927
01:00:52,616 --> 01:00:54,383
or it's too late.

928
01:00:54,384 --> 01:00:56,352
I want you to understand something,

929
01:00:56,353 --> 01:00:58,026
it is never too late.

930
01:00:58,722 --> 01:01:00,222
One of the barriers that I had

931
01:01:00,223 --> 01:01:01,724
in ever coming to God

932
01:01:01,725 --> 01:01:03,693
might be your problem, too.

933
01:01:03,694 --> 01:01:06,504
It was the image of my earthly father.

934
01:01:07,531 --> 01:01:08,831
You see, people would tell me that

935
01:01:08,832 --> 01:01:11,433
your heavenly father loves you,

936
01:01:11,434 --> 01:01:12,935
and that didn't bring joy into my life.

937
01:01:12,936 --> 01:01:14,236
That brought pain.

938
01:01:14,237 --> 01:01:15,443
You say, "Why?"

939
01:01:16,006 --> 01:01:21,006
Because I was not emotionally able to discern

940
01:01:22,612 --> 01:01:24,614
and an earthly father.

941
01:01:25,115 --> 01:01:28,961
Growing up to me - fathers hurt.

942
01:01:29,720 --> 01:01:31,700
One thing I had to realize, though,

943
01:01:32,255 --> 01:01:35,925
is that Christianity is not a religion,

944
01:01:35,926 --> 01:01:37,860
It's a relationship.

945
01:01:37,861 --> 01:01:39,862
You say, "what's the difference?"

946
01:01:39,863 --> 01:01:41,797
You see, a religion is men and women

947
01:01:41,798 --> 01:01:43,833
trying to work their way to God

948
01:01:43,834 --> 01:01:46,669
through good works and religious ritual.

949
01:01:46,670 --> 01:01:48,971
Christianity is God coming to us

950
01:01:48,972 --> 01:01:50,873
through his Son Jesus Christ

951
01:01:50,874 --> 01:01:53,411
offering us a relationship.

952
01:01:54,010 --> 01:01:56,412
Most people think that I came to Christ

953
01:01:56,413 --> 01:01:57,980
because of all the evidence

954
01:01:57,981 --> 01:02:01,016
that I've documented in my books.

955
01:02:01,017 --> 01:02:02,451
But none of that brought me to Christ,

956
01:02:02,452 --> 01:02:05,121
it only showed me that it was true.

957
01:02:05,122 --> 01:02:06,555
What really brought me to Christ

958
01:02:06,556 --> 01:02:08,058
was God's love.

959
01:02:08,692 --> 01:02:10,459
God loved me so much

960
01:02:10,460 --> 01:02:13,596
that if I were the only person alive,

961
01:02:13,597 --> 01:02:15,564
Christ would still die for me,

962
01:02:15,565 --> 01:02:17,666
and the same is true of you.

963
01:02:17,667 --> 01:02:18,634
You might be saying,

964
01:02:18,635 --> 01:02:22,471
"Josh, I want to know Christ personally.

965
01:02:22,472 --> 01:02:24,940
I want to know that I'm forgiven.

966
01:02:24,941 --> 01:02:27,176
I want to know that if I were to die today

967
01:02:27,177 --> 01:02:28,944
where I'd spend eternity."

968
01:02:28,945 --> 01:02:30,288
And you can.

969
01:02:31,715 --> 01:02:34,383
We come to Christ by faith

970
01:02:34,384 --> 01:02:36,152
through prayer, expressing that desire

971
01:02:36,153 --> 01:02:37,686
of our heart.

972
01:02:37,687 --> 01:02:39,488
And maybe the prayer that I prayed

973
01:02:39,489 --> 01:02:40,990
would help you

974
01:02:40,991 --> 01:02:43,793
to express that desire to God right now,

975
01:02:43,794 --> 01:02:45,796
to invite Christ into your life.

976
01:02:47,864 --> 01:02:49,832
I don't ask you to bow your heads.

977
01:02:49,833 --> 01:02:52,301
I don't even ask you to close your eyes.

978
01:02:52,302 --> 01:02:55,237
Because years ago, I learned the key to prayer

979
01:02:55,238 --> 01:02:57,640
is not in the position of the body,

980
01:02:57,641 --> 01:02:59,908
but in the attitude of the heart.

981
01:02:59,909 --> 01:03:02,111
This is a prayer that I prayed:

982
01:03:02,112 --> 01:03:05,881
"Lord Jesus, I need you.

983
01:03:05,882 --> 01:03:08,918
Thank you for dying on the cross for me.

984
01:03:08,919 --> 01:03:11,787
Forgive me and cleanse me.

985
01:03:11,788 --> 01:03:14,957
Right now, I trust you as Savior and Lord.

986
01:03:14,958 --> 01:03:17,126
Come into my life.

987
01:03:17,127 --> 01:03:19,995
Thank you that I can trust you.

988
01:03:19,996 --> 01:03:23,034
In Christ's Name. Amen."

989
01:03:23,934 --> 01:03:26,535
If you just prayed that prayer with me,

990
01:03:26,536 --> 01:03:28,311
and you were sincere,

991
01:03:28,972 --> 01:03:30,573
I want you in the next few days

992
01:03:30,574 --> 01:03:33,442
to find a follower of Jesus

993
01:03:33,443 --> 01:03:35,044
and share with him or her

994
01:03:35,045 --> 01:03:37,580
the decision you just made.

995
01:03:37,581 --> 01:03:39,848
And then do something that I did.

996
01:03:39,849 --> 01:03:41,217
Find a Bible,

997
01:03:41,218 --> 01:03:43,419
turn to the third Chapter of John,

998
01:03:43,420 --> 01:03:44,753
it's in the New Testament,

999
01:03:44,754 --> 01:03:47,857
Matthew, Mark, Luke and John

1000
01:03:47,858 --> 01:03:51,567
and read John 3, three times.

1001
01:03:52,462 --> 01:03:54,497
And then I want to help you grow.

1002
01:03:54,498 --> 01:03:55,965
I want to help you see Christ

1003
01:03:55,966 --> 01:03:59,034
truly change your life from the inside out.

1004
01:03:59,035 --> 01:04:00,669
Go to my website,

1005
01:04:00,670 --> 01:04:04,606
it's josh.org/undaunted.

1006
01:04:04,607 --> 01:04:08,411
Josh.org/undaunted

1007
01:04:08,412 --> 01:04:09,979
And I will be able to share with you

1008
01:04:09,980 --> 01:04:11,847
many things through my site

1009
01:04:11,848 --> 01:04:13,182
that can help you to see

1010
01:04:13,183 --> 01:04:16,218
God change your life forever.

1011
01:04:16,219 --> 01:04:19,421
Thank you so much for letting me be a part

1012
01:04:19,422 --> 01:04:24,422
of your life.